# Implementation Plan: LegalSaathi 2.0 Roadmap

This plan outlines a 20-feature expansion categorized into four strategic pillars: **User Experience**, **Legal Depth**, **Productivity**, and **Operational Excellence**.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> This is a long-term roadmap. We will prioritize features based on your feedback. 
> 
> **Proposed Phase 1 Focus**: PDF Export, Multilingual Support, and Evidence Matrix.

## Pillar 1: High-Fidelity User Experience
1.  **Pro PDF Export**: High-fidelity PDF generation using `react-pdf` with official legal formatting.
2.  **Multilingual Intake**: Real-time translation for 10+ regional Indian languages (Hindi, Tamil, etc.).
3.  **Voice-to-Case**: Integrated voice recording and transcription for hands-free case narration.
4.  **Legal Terms Glossary**: Interactive "Hover Tooltips" for complex legal jargon (e.g., *Habeas Corpus*).
5.  **Mobile PWA**: Transform the app into a Progressive Web App for home-screen access on mobile.

## Pillar 2: Deep Legal Intelligence
6.  **Evidence Matrix**: Automatically generated checklist of certificates/documents needed for each cited IPC section.
7.  **Timeline Visualizer**: An interactive chronological chart of events extracted from the case summary.
8.  **Jurisdiction Map**: Geolocation-based finder for the nearest relevant High Court or Police Station.
9.  **Precedent Heatmap**: Geographic visualization of where matched case laws originated.
10. **Interactive Q&A Agent**: A specialized follow-up chat specifically for the generated research results.

## Pillar 3: Productivity & Drafting
11. **Magistrate Templates**: Specialized draft formats for FIRs, Legal Notices, Bail Applications, and Petitions.
12. **Auto-Redaction**: A one-click tool to hide PII (Personally Identifiable Information) before sharing.
13. **Court Fee Calculator**: Automatic estimation of filing fees and stamp duties based on case type.
14. **Collaborative Review**: Secure "Share Links" for read-only access by secondary legal teams.
15. **Draft Versioning**: Version history to track how edits to the "Intake" summary affect the legal draft.

## Pillar 4: Operational & Security
16. **User Profiles/Auth**: Secure login using Clerk or Firebase to manage multiple case folders.
17. **Anonymous Mode**: Client-side data encryption for high-sensitivity legal consultations.
18. **e-Courts Integration**: Preliminary tracking of existing case status via PNR/Case Number.
19. **Advocate Marketplace**: A referral system connecting users to lawyers specialized in their specific case type.
20. **Dark/Glass Mode Toggle**: Enhanced UI themes for formal night-time legal research.

---

